# MinURL manual API requests for local debugging.
# Recommended extension: VS Code REST Client (humao.rest-client).
#
# Quick start:
# 1) Start server: go run ./cmd/minurl
# 2) Execute requests top-to-bottom.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8888
@seedShortID = 58twvV
@sampleOriginalURL = https://github.com/min0625

### Create short URL
# @name createShortURL
POST {{baseUrl}}/short-urls HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
  "original_url": "{{sampleOriginalURL}}"
}

### Get short URL by ID (from create response)
# If create request has not been executed yet, run the create request first.
GET {{baseUrl}}/short-urls/{{createShortURL.response.body.$.id}} HTTP/1.1

### Get short URL by fixed seed ID
# Useful when you want to verify a known ID quickly.
GET {{baseUrl}}/short-urls/{{seedShortID}} HTTP/1.1

### Not found example (expected HTTP 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/short-urls/NOT_FOUND_EXAMPLE HTTP/1.1
